Data Types:
-----------

Specify what type of data we are storing in the memory.

int age =30;

int -> data type (-ve to +ve)

age -> identifier/variable

= -> Assigment Operator

30 -> Value

Primitive :
-----------

Holds single values

Integer Category: (-ve to +ve without decimal)
-----------------

byte     1 byte
short    2 bytes
int      4 bytes
long     8 bytes

ex:100

Floating Point Category: (-ve to +ve with decimal)
------------------------

float      4 bytes
double     8 bytes

exL: 100.0



Character Category:    (Single Chracter)
---------------------

char       2 bytes

c

Boolean Catgeory:   (true or false)
-----------------

boolean    JVM dependent

true

Variable Dec:
-------------


datatype variableName;

int age;

Default values:
---------------

Integer Catgeory :  0
FLoating Point Category : 0.0
Character category : space
Boolean  : false


Variable Initialization:
------------------------
Assigning valuwe to a variable for the first time

   int age;
   age=30;




variable Assigment:
-------------------

Assigning valuwe to a variable from second time

int age;
age=30;
age=31;





class  DataTypesDemo{

  public static void main(String ar[]){
	  
	  
	  int employeeId ; //variable Dec
	  
	  employeeId=123; //variable Intialization
	  
	  System.out.println("Before Assigment employeeId is :"+employeeId);
	  
	  employeeId=124; //variable Assigmnet
	  
	   System.out.println("After Assigment employeeId is :"+employeeId);
 
  }

}


D:\60-JavaFullStack>javac DataTypesDemo.java

D:\60-JavaFullStack>java DataTypesDemo
Before Assigment employeeId is :123
After Assigment employeeId is :124


What happens when we declare a variable in Java?
-------------------------------------------


     double salary = 5000.0;



public class SecondProgram {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		
		System.out.println(Byte.SIZE);
		System.out.println(Short.SIZE);
		System.out.println(Integer.SIZE);
		System.out.println(Long.SIZE);
		

	}

}

